3 ways to use CSS.

1. Inline CSS. Example: <p color="red">Hello world<p>,, here color attribute is CSS used for styling.

2. With <style> tag inside <head></head> element. Example:

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>

    <style> <!--Like This-->
        body {
            background-color: yellow;
        }
    </style>  
</head>
<body></body>
</html>

3. Best way-- Linking CSS file in <head></head> with link tag. Example: 

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> <!--Like This-->
</head>
<body></body>
</html>









<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> <!--Like This-->
</head>
<body> parent
    <h1 class="heading" id="main-heading"></h1>child
    <p></p> sibling
</body>
</html>

